Searching For Passwords In Windows Configuration Files

# Windows Configuration Files

Configuration file 
It is a file that stores settings as it tell the system or the program
- How to run
- what values to see
- what options are set

Same thing applies to Windows
Windows also need to store things like - 
- User accounts
- passwords
- system setup
- installation setup 
These are stored in configuration files

These are just **files on disk** created during installation.

👉 They may contain:

- username
- password (sometimes readable)

From your PDF:

- Used for automated installation
- Can contain credentials
- May be base64 encoded

